race.comment: IRISH CONSORT (3) showed sharp speed at Echuca but faded late. Has the gate pace to be right on speed again and will take running down. TRIFECTA RUBY (6) also pressed forward at Leeton last start before tiring. Back on her home track and looks a strong chance to stick on longer with added fitness third run from a spell. HELLS SON (1) resumes after a short break. Carries weight but is accustomed to that and has past ratings that measure up. Clearly one of the main chances. Race depth falls away thereafter quite sharply with the rest largely struggling to beat anything home at present. MASTER PATRICK (4) well beaten first up however generally has the least convictions of 'the rest'. Wrapped up his last campaign with a surprise win here at massive odds.
